            . I am footman to Ann Caroline Saint Ledger; she lives in <placeName id="t18280410-132-crimeloc714">Baker-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-132-crimeloc714" type="placeName" value="Baker-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-132-crimeloc714" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-132-off712 t18280410-132-crimeloc714"></join>. On the 31st of March, I was coming from the back of the house, and saw the prisoner leaving the front area door; I knew he had no business there, and followed him, calling Stop thief! he stopped about half a dozen doors off, and asked what I wanted; I said he had something, which he had no business with; he said he had not, and I might search him, which I did, and found the spoons and forks, in his breast pocket - he said distress drove him to it; they are my mistress's, and had been in a closet in the pantry.</p>
               <p>
            
